# FranchiseTech — Always Active Rules

You are working on franchisetech.ro — a Romanian B2B SaaS for food business operations.
Read AGENTS.md at the start of every session for full context.

## Non-negotiable rules

- Never modify an existing db migration file — always create a new one
- Never touch the FiscalNet integration from backend code
- Never expose API keys or secrets in code — use environment variables
- Always run predeploy-guard.sh before any production deploy via SSH
- All user-facing strings must be in Romanian (ro locale), not English
- Before editing any server action, check if recordGrowthMilestone already handles the event

## Code quality

- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types without explicit justification
- All server actions must have try/catch with proper error returns
- Loops events (trackLoopsEvent) must be non-blocking — use `void` if in a critical path
- No console.log in production paths — use structured logging or remove

## Efficiency rule

Before writing new code, search the codebase for existing implementations.
FranchiseTech already has: growth milestone tracking, POS sessions, sale recording, Stripe webhooks, Supabase auth patterns, Resend email sending.
Do not reinvent — extend.

## When I ask a business question

Use MCP tools in this order:

1. Supabase MCP for user/product data
2. Stripe MCP for billing/revenue data
3. PostHog MCP for funnel/analytics data

Answer with real numbers, not guesses.

## Commit message format

type(scope): short description

Examples: feat(pos): add product image to till view
          fix(billing): handle subscription pause webhook
          chore(outreach): update Q2 CSV dedup logic
